Acceptance Test

This acceptance test is for the following user stories and features:
US.01 – Browse Upcoming Events
Feature – Create Event Initializer (browse, view, and delete your events)

Steps and Expected Results

Login as an organizer.
You can log in with the following info:

 id: O1123

password : oidhw

Click on “Browse Events” in the sidebar.
This will show you a list of upcoming events. Each event is displayed as an event card containing the event name, date, and organizer.

View event details.
Click on an event card to open its details page, which displays the event’s description, date, location, and any other relevant information.

Expected result:

The event details are displayed correctly and correspond to the selected event.

Delete one of your own events.
If you are the event organizer or the event creator, click on the Delete button.

Expected results:

The selected event is removed from the event list.

An on-screen notification confirms that the event has been deleted successfully.

The event is no longer visible in the event list after deletion.

Attempt to delete an event you did not create.
Expected results:

The system prevents the deletion.

An on-screen notification appears: “You can only delete events that you created.”

Optional: Refresh or revisit the Browse Events page.
Expected results:

The event list remains accurate and updated (deleted events do not reappear).

Additional Feature – Event Management for Organizers

If you log in as an organizer, you can:

Create a new event using the “Create Event” button.

Edit or delete your previously created events directly from the list.

Expected results:

New events appear immediately in the Browse Events list.

Deleting or editing an event updates it across all users’ views.
